<h1>Dave Donaldson</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://arcware.net/now/">arcware.net/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Columbus
OH
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Application Architect at Questline, a digital communication and technology company that services the utility industry.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I design and build stuff that help make other peoples' jobs a little bit better.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I love to build software and applications, plain and simple. It's equal parts engineering and art with no end to creativity.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Having just turned 40 with a kid about to graduate high school, all the startups, valuations, and money being made by other people are insignificant compared to the people close to you.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
"Creativity, Inc" by Ed Catmull
</p>

